The Proposal: -

The Director of Education (Schemes), Maharashtra State, Pune has issued a circular to the Department of School Education, Government of Maharashtra, regarding the release of sanctioned funds of the year 2024-25 on the BDS system for educational scholarship schemes. 1 here. The request was made in a letter dated 05.07.2024.

Accordingly, the Finance Department. According to the limit set by the circular dated 25.07.2024 for target-wise expenditure for fund disbursement, Rs. The funds have been disbursed as per the Government Decision dated 06.08.2024. At present, 80 per cent of the sanctioned funds under the 34 - Scholarship / Scholarships target has been made available for disbursement.

Accordingly, to encourage meritorious students of the state to pursue education, the Finance Department was under the consideration of the Government to disburse funds under the 34 - Scholarship / Scholarship Scheme amounting to 80% of the total sanctioned funds in this financial year.

Government Decisions: - To promote meritorious students in the state, various schemes are in operation to provide scholarships to students in schools in the state. In this financial year, the government was contemplating to disburse funds from the budgeted provision in the proportion of 80% of the budgeted sanctioned provision as made available for disbursement by the Finance Department.

2. For the schemes mentioned in paragraph 3 below 34 - Scholarship / Scholarship, the total amount is 28,29,42, 500 / - (letter Rs. The Government is approving the release of funds to the tune of ₹23.9 million (SaaS 500 only) and making these funds available on the Budgetary Distribution System.
